I'm disappointed that ExxonMobil continues to sponsor the Iditarod, knowing that dogs suffer when forced through blinding snowstorms in subzero temperatures over grueling Alaskan terrain. More than 150 dogs died as a result of the race.

A PETA investigator worked in two kennels owned by former Iditarod champions and found that dogs were denied veterinary care for painful injuries, were constantly chained next to dilapidated boxes and plastic barrels in a freezing cold, and forced to run even when exhausted and dehydrated. .

In the 2020 race alone, more than 220 dogs were taken off the trail due to exhaustion, illness, injury or other reasons. Please stop associating your business with this deadly event.
